#: ../../git.md:8
msgid "Working with Git in Remix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:10
msgid "In Remix, you can initialize Git for version control in your workspaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:12
msgid "Connecting to GitHub"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:14
msgid "Before you can use Git in any of your workspaces, you have to login with GitHub using the \"**Login with GitHub**\" button on the Top Bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:16
msgid "![Remix Top Bar showing login with GitHub button.](images/git/login-with-github.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:16
msgid "Remix Top Bar showing login with GitHub button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:18
msgid "Alternatively, you can add username and email to the Github section of the Git plugin. You can find the Git plugin on the Icon Panel represented by a branch icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:20
msgid "![Git plugin settings.](images/git/gh-login-manually.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:20
msgid "Git plugin settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:22
msgid "Git operations in Remix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:24
msgid "Initializing Git in a Workspace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:26
msgid "For information about initializing a workspace, see the section about initializing Git on the {ref}`Remix Workspaces <workspaces:initializing a workspace with git>` page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:28
msgid "Cloning an existing repository into Remix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:30
msgid "You can clone an existing repository from GitHub into Remix using \"**CLONE**\" accordion item in the Git plugin. You can clone a repository by loading it from GitHub using the \"**Load from GitHub**\" button and selecting one from your list of public repositories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:32
msgid "Alternatively, you can clone a repository by providing its URL in the \"**CLONE FROM URL**\" text box. When you clone a repository, Remix initializes it as a separate Workspace. See {doc}`Remix Workspaces <workspaces>` to learn more about Workspaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:35
msgid "Remix stores your files in the browser and browser storage is limited. Cloning a repository that is too large will cause the Remix IDE. This is why you have to manually specify the depth and branches you want to clone. If you are using {doc}`Remixd </remixd>` you don't have to worry about cloning large repositories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:38
msgid "![Remix Git plugin clone section.](images/git/gh-clone.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:38
#: ../../git.md:44
msgid "Remix Git plugin clone section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:40
msgid "Committing changes to Git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:42
msgid "You can commit the changes you made to your current Workspace using the \"**SOURCE CONTROL**\" accordion item in the Git plugin. Stage files individually using the plus icon next to them or all at once using the plus icon on the \"**Changes**\" dropdown label. Enter commit messages in the text box and commit the staged changes using the \"**Commit**\" button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:44
msgid "![Remix Git plugin clone section.](images/git/gh-commit.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:46
msgid "Adding a remote repository"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:48
msgid "You can add a remote repository to your Workspace on Remix using the \"**REMOTE**\" accordion item by either loading from GitHub or adding it manually using a remote URL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:50
msgid "![Remix Git plugin highlighting the REMOTE tool.](images/git/gh-remote-repo.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:50
msgid "Remix Git plugin highlighting the REMOTE tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:52
msgid "Running common commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:54
msgid "The Git plugin has limited support for Git commands, as of Remix v0.70, you can run the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:56
msgid "`git push`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:57
msgid "`git push --force`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:58
msgid "`git fetch`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:59
msgid "`git pull`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:61
msgid "You can run these commands through the \"**COMMANDS**\" accordion item in the Git plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:63
msgid "![Remix Git plugin showing common Git commands.](images/git/gh-git-commands.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:63
msgid "Remix Git plugin showing common Git commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../git.md:66
msgid "You can view the output of some of these commands on the \"**LOGS**\" accordion item."
msgstr ""

